what is a really great tasting beef stew recipe mines usually turns out tasting terrible i've actually tried this and it is amazing the ultimate beef stew recipe courtesy tyler florence show tyler's ultimate episode stew to pounds beef shoulder cut into inch pieces fresh thyme sprigs plus sprigs carrots cut into inch slices garlic cloves smashed cups blanched and peeled red pearl onions orange peel cut in large strips cloves a few teaspoon whole black peppercorns bay leaves bottle good quality dry red wine recommended burgundy cup extra virgin olive oil for frying plus more to drizzle tablespoons butter sea salt and freshly ground black pepper bouquet garni cups beef stock pound baby carrots pound garden peas pound white mushrooms cut in half pinch sugar fresh flat leaf parsley chopped as garnish chives finely chopped as garnish garlic puree recipe follows croutons recipe follows serving suggestion buttery mashed potatoes with chives and warm croutons with garlic puree to make the marinade place the beef in a large glass or plastic container add sprigs of thyme carrots garlic red onions orange peel cloves peppercorns bay leaves and the wine mix well to coat then cover and refrigerate for hours remove beef from the marinade and blot dry on paper towels heat the oil and butter and the remaining sprigs thyme in a heavy bottomed saucepan on a high heat when the oil begins to smoke remove the thyme add the beef and brown evenly on all sides season with salt and freshly ground black pepper strain the marinade into the beef and stir with a wooden spoon scraping up the flavorful bits in the bottom of the pot add bouquet garni and beef stock bring to a simmer and cook uncovered until the liquid starts to thicken about to minutes cover and cook on low heat for hours after about hours add the baby carrots garden peas and mushrooms along with a pinch of sugar to balance out the acid from the red wine turn the heat up slightly and simmer uncovered for minutes more until the vegetables and meat are tender season with salt and pepper garnish with chopped parsley and chives squeeze some of the roasted garlic onto the croutons drizzle with extra virgin olive oil and serve with the stew garlic puree heads garlic cut in half horizontally tablespoons olive oil sprig thyme salt and pepper preheat oven to degrees f put garlic on a sheet of aluminum foil drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and freshly ground black pepper add a sprig of thyme and fold the foil around the garlic cook for to minutes or until garlic is tender and golden brown croutons olive oil for frying slices bread heat about inch of the olive oil in a frying pan when the oil is hot add the bread in batches and fry until golden on both sides about minute per side remove from pan and dry on paper towels Garlic Cuisine of Singapore Salad Idli Brewery Coriander Wine Cooking Sauerkraut Nabemono Cincinnati chili Fish sauce Food preservation Fish and chips Pasta Meatball Sushi Ham Cuisine of Malaysia Olive oil Tamale Stir frying Martini cocktail Cuisine of Cambodia Kebab D__ner kebab Cuisine of Turkey Common bean Onion Bagel Roman eating and drinking Sandwich Cuisine of Argentina Gazpacho Chocolate Hot pot 